14:35.167 --> 14:36.752
[strains]

14:36.752 --> 14:39.588
Join us!
My mother is queen now.

14:39.588 --> 14:42.674
She can make you a knight.
You can be my boyfriend.

14:42.674 --> 14:45.719
And if we work as a couple,
you know, travel well together,

14:45.719 --> 14:47.304
see how cohabitation goes.

14:47.304 --> 14:50.641
Who knows?
You could be king one day.

14:50.641 --> 14:51.934
[thwack]

14:51.934 --> 14:54.311
[glass tinkling]

14:55.354 --> 14:57.731
[Patrick gasps]

14:57.731 --> 15:01.818
‐ So, you really feel that way about me?
You weren't just using me?

15:02.903 --> 15:07.950
‐ Oh, you weren't even a part of my plan.
You were just a happy accident.

15:07.950 --> 15:09.952
I liked hanging out with you.

15:09.952 --> 15:11.620
‐ God dammit. I...

15:11.620 --> 15:12.621
[sighs]

15:12.621 --> 15:14.540
I liked it too.

15:14.540 --> 15:17.167
‐ It doesn't matter who sits
on the throne.

15:17.167 --> 15:21.421
Kings and queens come and go,
but they're all the same.

15:22.214 --> 15:23.215
‐ [sighs]

15:23.215 --> 15:26.969
And Merriman is
an objectively terrible ruler.

15:26.969 --> 15:29.054
The people are suffering.

15:29.054 --> 15:31.765
‐ Exactly.
You'd be doing the right thing.

15:31.765 --> 15:32.975
For everybody.

15:32.975 --> 15:36.228
Plus you'd get to see me naked.

15:36.228 --> 15:37.187
‐ [Patrick moans]

15:37.187 --> 15:39.857
That does sound like a win‐win.

15:42.359 --> 15:44.069
Oh...

15:48.615 --> 15:49.783
‐ Yaaa!

15:50.909 --> 15:52.953
Well, that was annoying.

15:52.953 --> 15:54.037
‐ Alright, fun's over.

15:54.037 --> 15:56.957
Let's go commit some crimes
to balance out the good deed.

15:56.957 --> 16:00.294
‐ Time for Operation Steal Stuff
We're Gonna Steal

16:00.294 --> 16:03.172
Before We Got Sidetracked
By Personal Growth.

16:03.172 --> 16:04.214
[clown horn honks]

16:05.883 --> 16:10.345
‐ I mean, I bet I'd get a lot more respect
at home if I were king.

16:10.345 --> 16:13.515
‐ And it could happen
sooner than you think.

16:13.515 --> 16:17.436
Mother could always catch a bad case
of fall‐down‐the‐stairs‐itis,

16:17.436 --> 16:18.687
if you know what I mean.

16:18.687 --> 16:22.274
‐ [gasps]
You'd kill your own mother?

16:22.274 --> 16:23.901
No. I'm sorry.

16:23.901 --> 16:26.820
I swore an oath
and I'm not going back on it.

16:26.820 --> 16:31.742
Promises don't seem to mean
that much to you, but they do to me!

16:31.742 --> 16:33.452
Haaaa!

16:33.452 --> 16:36.830
‐ You dickhead!
Now you're never gonna see me naked.

16:36.830 --> 16:38.123
Think about that.

16:38.123 --> 16:39.458
‐ Haaaa!

16:43.086 --> 16:45.923
Give up. Your people
are getting their asses kicked.

16:45.923 --> 16:49.593
And once the army hears you've attacked
the castle, they'll return to help.

16:49.593 --> 16:50.677
You can't win.

16:50.677 --> 16:52.971
‐ Yes, I can! [chuckles]

16:52.971 --> 16:55.015
I'll blow up the royal family!

16:55.015 --> 16:58.101
And I already killed everyone else
in the line of succession.

16:58.101 --> 16:59.269
So guess what?

16:59.269 --> 17:03.065
It's gonna be Mother
or it's gonna be nobody!

17:03.065 --> 17:04.650
‐ Arggh!

17:06.401 --> 17:07.444
‐ [gasps] No!

17:11.365 --> 17:13.242
[boom!]

17:13.242 --> 17:15.494
‐ [screaming]
‐ What the fuck?!

17:20.082 --> 17:23.293
‐ Holy fucking asscrackers!

17:25.504 --> 17:28.090
‐ Blossom!
‐ Sweetheart. Are you alright?

17:28.090 --> 17:29.550
‐ I'm still alive, Mom.

17:29.550 --> 17:32.928
Don't make such a big deal
out of everything. God.

17:32.928 --> 17:34.680
[screaming] Mama!

17:34.680 --> 17:37.933
‐ Sorry, darling,
I'm busy not making a big deal out of it.

17:37.933 --> 17:38.851
[sword clangs]

17:38.851 --> 17:39.768
KING MERRIMAN:
Patrick!

17:43.939 --> 17:45.691
[straining]

17:45.691 --> 17:47.609
‐ Argggh!

17:49.111 --> 17:51.905
‐ Ha‐ha!
‐ Yeah! Kill her, Patrick.

17:51.905 --> 17:53.448
‐ Curb‐stomp her!

17:53.448 --> 17:55.075
[castle rumbling]

17:55.868 --> 17:57.119
‐ Yaaa!
‐ [gasps]

17:58.412 --> 17:59.955
[gasping]

18:04.168 --> 18:05.919
‐ Give up, Danielle.

18:05.919 --> 18:08.463
‐ Give up? I already won.

18:08.463 --> 18:10.424
Once this tower falls,

18:10.424 --> 18:15.804
the only heir to the throne
still alive will be Mother!

18:15.804 --> 18:18.223
‐ It's a perfect plan, sweetheart.

18:18.223 --> 18:20.726
‐ Mother?
What the fuck are you doing up here?

18:20.726 --> 18:22.102
‐ I came back for Daniel.

18:22.102 --> 18:25.314
‐ Oh! You're ruining everything!

18:25.314 --> 18:26.565
PATRICK:
Huh?

18:26.565 --> 18:28.692
[castle rumbling]

18:29.776 --> 18:31.737
‐ Fine. Go ahead and die, Mother.

18:31.737 --> 18:33.989
That means I'm heir to the throne.

18:33.989 --> 18:35.365
Squirrel wings!

18:35.365 --> 18:36.950
Huhhh!

18:36.950 --> 18:40.162
Raised in a circus, bitch!

18:40.871 --> 18:42.539
‐ Waaaa!

18:45.042 --> 18:47.044
‐ Guess we're doing this, then.

18:48.212 --> 18:49.838
Squirrel wings!

18:49.838 --> 18:51.256
Aaaaah!

18:51.256 --> 18:54.510
‐ Fashion show! Fashion show...

18:54.510 --> 18:59.806
‐ [scatting burlesque melody]
‐ [ladies‐in‐waiting cheering]

18:59.806 --> 19:01.099
[Donna screaming]

19:03.310 --> 19:05.521
‐ Hey, look, that lady's flying.

19:07.981 --> 19:09.441
[knocking]

19:10.651 --> 19:13.237
‐ [screaming] Take Human Shield!

19:13.237 --> 19:14.279
‐ What?

19:14.279 --> 19:17.157
‐ Did you guys know there's
a hidden passageway back here?

19:17.157 --> 19:20.911
‐ Grab whatever's not nailed down
and follow us.

19:21.620 --> 19:22.538
‐ Hmm.

19:22.538 --> 19:23.956
Hmm?

19:23.956 --> 19:25.958
‐ [laughing]
‐ Yes!

19:25.958 --> 19:29.962
‐ There goes my sister.
Always making it about her.

19:29.962 --> 19:32.422
[castle rumbling]

19:33.257 --> 19:35.092
‐ Hurry.
Into the shit chute!

19:36.009 --> 19:37.886
‐ I'm gonna take the stairs.

19:37.886 --> 19:40.222
‐ Get in that fucking toilet!
‐ [Princess screaming]

19:40.222 --> 19:41.265
[screaming]

19:41.265 --> 19:44.142
‐ Patrick, since we're
probably going to die,

19:44.142 --> 19:48.856
I want you to know,
you're like the son I never had.

19:48.856 --> 19:50.732
‐ Thank you, Sire.

19:50.732 --> 19:54.111
‐ I should specify: the son I never had,
that I am aware of.

19:54.111 --> 19:55.153
‐ Right.

19:55.153 --> 19:57.447
‐ I get around, Patrick.
‐ Sire, please jump.

19:58.323 --> 19:59.783
‐ Yaa! [screaming]

19:59.783 --> 20:00.784
[castle rumbling]

20:00.784 --> 20:02.077
[Patrick screaming]

20:02.077 --> 20:03.996
[castle rumbling]

20:09.418 --> 20:12.171
‐ Oh my god.
The royal family.

20:12.171 --> 20:14.214
‐ Designated survivor, baby!

20:15.674 --> 20:17.342
‐ [coughing]

20:17.342 --> 20:18.802
Fuck!

20:18.802 --> 20:21.263
[King gasps, splutters]

20:21.263 --> 20:23.640
‐ Your majesties.
You're alive!

20:23.640 --> 20:26.351
‐ Yes, the expression I'm making
doesn't mean I'm not thrilled.

20:26.351 --> 20:28.478
I'm‐I'm‐I'm thrilled.

20:29.271 --> 20:30.606
‐ Has anyone seen Patrick?

20:31.773 --> 20:33.192
‐ Patrick.

20:38.822 --> 20:39.907
[Patrick gasps]

20:39.907 --> 20:41.408
RUBEN: There he is!
CORAL: Patrick!

20:41.408 --> 20:43.118
‐ Oh, he's fine.

20:43.118 --> 20:44.578
‐ Buddy, you did it.

20:44.578 --> 20:45.913
‐ Everyone.

20:45.913 --> 20:49.499
Do not drink the moat water.

20:49.499 --> 20:52.669
It links directly to the sewage system.

20:57.424 --> 21:00.677
‐ This is so gross,
but I can't stop looking at it.

21:00.677 --> 21:02.846
‐ Where were you, dumb whores?

21:02.846 --> 21:04.306
You're supposed to protect me.

21:04.306 --> 21:08.644
‐ Oh, whoops.
You should probably fire us.

21:08.644 --> 21:09.895
‐ No way.

21:09.895 --> 21:12.356
God as my witness, Human Shield,

21:12.356 --> 21:14.816
you will die protecting me.

21:17.569 --> 21:20.030
‐ Oh. Hello, Ruben.

21:20.030 --> 21:22.950
‐ Holden. How's your fiancée?

21:24.117 --> 21:26.578
‐ Donna, stop being so dramatic.
Get up.

21:28.789 --> 21:30.290
PATRICK:
Oh my god.

21:30.290 --> 21:32.125
Today was a disaster.

21:32.125 --> 21:33.210
‐ Eh, maybe.

21:33.210 --> 21:35.128
But you should be proud
of yourself, Patrick.

21:35.128 --> 21:36.129
‐ Proud?

21:36.129 --> 21:38.423
‐ You killed the Minotaur,
defeated the assassin,

21:38.423 --> 21:40.551
and rescued the whole
fuckin' royal family.

21:41.176 --> 21:43.554
‐ Huh. I guess I did all that, huh?

21:43.554 --> 21:46.265
Am I actually good at this job?

21:46.265 --> 21:47.349
‐ You know what?

21:47.349 --> 21:50.185
I hereby take you off my shart list.

21:50.185 --> 21:52.855
‐ [gasps] I'm a good squire.

21:52.855 --> 21:54.690
This is the greatest day of my life.

21:54.690 --> 21:56.817
‐ And here I had you pegged as the squire

21:56.817 --> 21:58.944
most likely to cut his own head off
by accident.

21:58.944 --> 22:01.780
‐ Who's at the top of that list now? Huh?

22:03.031 --> 22:04.449
Is it me?

22:05.617 --> 22:07.160
It's me, isn't it?

22:08.370 --> 22:10.497
Yeah... [chuckles]

22:10.497 --> 22:11.832
...it's me.

22:11.832 --> 22:13.041
Nice.

22:15.794 --> 22:17.212
[raven croaking]

22:17.212 --> 22:20.674
‐ Thinks he'll put his daddy
out to pasture, eh?

22:20.674 --> 22:26.555
When I escape this gilded cage,
sonny boy's gonna reap the whirlwind.

22:26.555 --> 22:31.310
He's gonna enter a hell
previously unknown to mankind.

22:32.519 --> 22:35.898
I wonder if any
of those snickerdoodles are left.

22:35.898 --> 22:37.274
[door clatters]

22:37.274 --> 22:39.109
‐ Hello, Gramps.

22:39.109 --> 22:40.194
[Old King gasps]

22:42.196 --> 22:43.822
♪ dramatic fanfare plays ♪

22:45.032 --> 22:46.742
♪ theme song playing ♪

23:18.273 --> 23:20.150
CHILD:
That was amazing.

23:20.150 --> 23:21.318
[ball beeping]

23:21.318 --> 23:22.903
[loser sound effect plays]
